1800 BC  
CH… Cretan hieroglyphs are a hieroglyphic writing system used in early Bronze Age Crete, during the Minoan era. They predate Linear A by about a century, but the two writing systems continued to be used in parallel for most of their history.  

Languages	Unknown; possibly "Minoan"  

Signs look markedly different with font Aegean, see abc/Cretan.html

[Anatolian](Anatolian.html) Hieroglyphs ≠  

Linear CH Cretan Hieroglyphs ≠

N	 ? na 	󲇝 ne?	󲋎 ni 	󲃩 no 	󲂏 nu  [ 󲁾 󲃐 󲂂 󲂜 󲅓 vs zo]
